00:00:20.322 --> 00:00:22.780 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: The notion
of any absolute good and evil

00:00:22.780 --> 00:00:25.540 align:middle line:10%
seems to become an archaic
thought in a world driven

00:00:25.540 --> 00:00:27.550 align:middle line:10%
by preference and relativism.

00:00:27.550 --> 00:00:28.780 align:middle line:90%
But is it?

00:00:28.780 --> 00:00:31.240 align:middle line:84%
Hermeticist and modern day
philosopher Neil Kramer

00:00:31.240 --> 00:00:32.080 align:middle line:90%
is back with us.

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
talk about the basics,

00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:37.240 align:middle line:84%
the nature of good and
evil, right and wrong.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:39.610 align:middle line:84%
And this is really
unpopular because it's

00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:41.060 align:middle line:90%
an anything-goes world.

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:41.860 align:middle line:90%
And we know that.

00:00:41.860 --> 00:00:45.160 align:middle line:84%
We've seen this through a
lot of phenomena going on

00:00:45.160 --> 00:00:46.130 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:00:46.130 --> 00:00:48.670 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has their own notion
of what reality is now,

00:00:48.670 --> 00:00:52.270 align:middle line:84%
where we used to have more
kind of consensus reality.

00:00:52.270 --> 00:00:55.280 align:middle line:84%
One can argue whether that's
a good thing or a bad thing.

00:00:55.280 --> 00:00:58.180 align:middle line:84%
But I think we need to go
even deeper into the basics.

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:02.440 align:middle line:84%
So Neil, thank you for gracing
us with your presence again.

00:01:02.440 --> 00:01:06.020 align:middle line:90%
And let's start with reality.

00:01:06.020 --> 00:01:07.310 align:middle line:90%
What does reality even mean?

00:01:07.310 --> 00:01:09.730 align:middle line:90%
And what is reality to you?

00:01:09.730 --> 00:01:14.530 align:middle line:10%
>>NEIL KRAMER: Reality is what
is real, and only what is real.

00:01:14.530 --> 00:01:16.880 align:middle line:10%
It's not a personal creation.

00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:18.610 align:middle line:90%
It's not your interface.

00:01:18.610 --> 00:01:20.140 align:middle line:90%
It's the world.

00:01:20.140 --> 00:01:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Reality is the
world that is real.

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:26.600 align:middle line:84%
It reveals itself only
to those who seek it.

00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:29.890 align:middle line:84%
So I would say most people
that we meet in our lives, most

00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:32.500 align:middle line:84%
people we cross in
the street, most

00:01:32.500 --> 00:01:36.580 align:middle line:84%
people in spiritual communities
and in materialist communities

00:01:36.580 --> 00:01:38.250 align:middle line:90%
don't know what reality is.

00:01:38.250 --> 00:01:41.320 align:middle line:84%
They move in it, but
they don't see it.

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:43.660 align:middle line:84%
So it only reveals
itself to those

00:01:43.660 --> 00:01:48.760 align:middle line:84%
who pursue it because it is an
inherently supernatural thing.

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:49.900 align:middle line:90%
It's material aspect.

00:01:49.900 --> 00:01:52.050 align:middle line:90%
It's slight.

00:01:52.050 --> 00:01:54.503 align:middle line:84%
It's real nature
is supernatural,

00:01:54.503 --> 00:01:56.170 align:middle line:84%
which is why most
people don't pursue it

00:01:56.170 --> 00:01:58.510 align:middle line:90%
because it is a divine thing.

00:01:58.510 --> 00:02:00.467 align:middle line:84%
So if you don't
accept that, it's

00:02:00.467 --> 00:02:02.050 align:middle line:84%
going to limit you
from the beginning.

00:02:02.050 --> 00:02:05.650 align:middle line:84%
So the pursuit of
truth will lead you

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:09.820 align:middle line:84%
to reality over a
century, over 100 years.

00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:13.450 align:middle line:84%
So you're not going to see it
fully until you're 60, 70, 80.

00:02:13.450 --> 00:02:15.700 align:middle line:84%
Prior to that, you're
going to see a little bit.

00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:17.830 align:middle line:84%
Reality is the real
world and nothing else.

00:02:17.830 --> 00:02:19.240 align:middle line:90%
And it's one thing.

00:02:19.240 --> 00:02:21.335 align:middle line:90%
And it's the same for everybody.

00:02:21.335 --> 00:02:22.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it sounds
like what you're

00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:25.030 align:middle line:84%
saying is to see
reality, we have

00:02:25.030 --> 00:02:28.690 align:middle line:84%
to see the unseen building
blocks and constructs that

00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.895 align:middle line:90%
actually make reality.

00:02:30.895 --> 00:02:32.770 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: You have to
see what is real first.

00:02:32.770 --> 00:02:34.270 align:middle line:90%
You have to see the trees.

00:02:34.270 --> 00:02:36.220 align:middle line:84%
You have to see the
mountains and rivers.

00:02:36.220 --> 00:02:38.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: By the five
sense world real.

00:02:38.430 --> 00:02:39.230 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Sure.

00:02:39.230 --> 00:02:44.170 align:middle line:84%
So you have to understand first,
the natural creation is here.

00:02:44.170 --> 00:02:46.690 align:middle line:84%
How real it is is a
slightly different question.

00:02:46.690 --> 00:02:47.830 align:middle line:90%
But it's here.

00:02:47.830 --> 00:02:52.960 align:middle line:84%
And it symbolizes and
typifies what is actual.

00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:54.940 align:middle line:84%
So that's the
beginning place which

00:02:54.940 --> 00:02:59.530 align:middle line:84%
is why it's very smart and wise
to draw young minds and hearts

00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:01.990 align:middle line:90%
to nature and education.

00:03:01.990 --> 00:03:05.200 align:middle line:84%
So let's look at nature,
because that's going to tell us

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.730 align:middle line:90%
something that's real.

00:03:06.730 --> 00:03:09.940 align:middle line:84%
Whereas the city,
the suburban life,

00:03:09.940 --> 00:03:12.760 align:middle line:84%
the mainstream culture
is not going to do that.

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:15.190 align:middle line:84%
It's going to lead you
away from what is real.

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.350 align:middle line:90%
Nature symbolizes reality.

00:03:17.350 --> 00:03:21.850 align:middle line:84%
Nature shows us something
toward the creator.

00:03:21.850 --> 00:03:26.060 align:middle line:84%
That's a starting point,
is to examine its presence.

00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:27.850 align:middle line:84%
As to the purpose
and nature of that,

00:03:27.850 --> 00:03:29.330 align:middle line:90%
that's a different question.

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:30.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:30.130 --> 00:03:31.922 align:middle line:84%
And we can get into
that whenever you like.

00:03:31.922 --> 00:03:33.880 align:middle line:84%
But let's go to the
next part first,

00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:36.130 align:middle line:84%
which is the new
age nostrum that we

00:03:36.130 --> 00:03:37.470 align:middle line:90%
can create our own reality.

00:03:37.470 --> 00:03:38.470 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah, garbage.

00:03:38.470 --> 00:03:39.845 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that
is essentially

00:03:39.845 --> 00:03:41.630 align:middle line:90%
where everybody's living.

00:03:41.630 --> 00:03:42.770 align:middle line:90%
We're all in our own movie.

00:03:42.770 --> 00:03:43.570 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:03:43.570 --> 00:03:45.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's very
hard to move anything

00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:48.580 align:middle line:84%
of a coherent and
constructive nature forward

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:51.670 align:middle line:84%
when you can't get anyone
in the same place thinking

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:54.230 align:middle line:84%
in a similar way at the same
time, perceiving reality

00:03:54.230 --> 00:03:55.030 align:middle line:90%
the same way.

00:03:55.030 --> 00:03:55.830 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:03:55.830 --> 00:03:58.490 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, well, if reality
is only what is real,

00:03:58.490 --> 00:04:02.320 align:middle line:84%
then that makes us all in a
quite inequitable place, which

00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:05.110 align:middle line:84%
is to say, it's a
level playing field.

00:04:05.110 --> 00:04:07.405 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has the same
access to reality.

00:04:07.405 --> 00:04:08.780 align:middle line:84%
If you're born,
and you're alive,

00:04:08.780 --> 00:04:10.780 align:middle line:90%
and you can think and feel--

00:04:10.780 --> 00:04:12.430 align:middle line:90%
which most people can--

00:04:12.430 --> 00:04:15.130 align:middle line:84%
you have total
access to reality.

00:04:15.130 --> 00:04:18.910 align:middle line:84%
And the truth of that
reality is available.

00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:22.270 align:middle line:84%
It's a really strange thing to
say that truth is available.

00:04:22.270 --> 00:04:25.300 align:middle line:84%
Today, unlike any other
period in human history

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:28.480 align:middle line:84%
that I can think of,
the truth is there

00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:32.830 align:middle line:84%
to find in any walk of life--
political, social, cultural,

00:04:32.830 --> 00:04:36.370 align:middle line:84%
artistic, spiritual,
physiological, nutritional--

00:04:36.370 --> 00:04:40.030 align:middle line:84%
whatever you care to think
of, truth is available.

00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:43.510 align:middle line:84%
And if people want that
truth, they can go to it.

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And you have to develop
a field of expertise.

00:04:46.070 --> 00:04:47.980 align:middle line:84%
You can't know
all truth, but you

00:04:47.980 --> 00:04:50.600 align:middle line:84%
can focus on the things
that are most important.

00:04:50.600 --> 00:04:52.360 align:middle line:84%
Most people don't
want the truth.

00:04:52.360 --> 00:04:55.630 align:middle line:84%
What they want is
to settle instead

00:04:55.630 --> 00:04:57.987 align:middle line:90%
for a very satisfying fantasy.

00:04:57.987 --> 00:05:00.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, like a
reflection of their desires

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:00.940 align:middle line:90%
being manifest.

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:01.180 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:05:01.180 --> 00:05:02.560 align:middle line:84%
So they'll say, well,
I'm glad you've got

00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:03.730 align:middle line:90%
your reality and your truth.

00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's cool, because I've
got my reality and my truth.

00:05:06.490 --> 00:05:10.990 align:middle line:84%
That's the sign of a fantasist
who has found not truth,

00:05:10.990 --> 00:05:14.570 align:middle line:84%
but a very comfortable
delusional state in which they

00:05:14.570 --> 00:05:15.370 align:middle line:90%
can dwell.

00:05:15.370 --> 00:05:18.840 align:middle line:84%
Now some people, I have to
say, do that rather pleasingly

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:21.207 align:middle line:90%
and rather harmlessly.

00:05:21.207 --> 00:05:22.290 align:middle line:90%
And some of those people--

00:05:22.290 --> 00:05:23.665 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's none
of my business.

00:05:23.665 --> 00:05:26.760 align:middle line:84%
If they want to do that, they
can do that all day long.

00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:29.190 align:middle line:84%
Many people, though, do
that in a harmful way

00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:31.440 align:middle line:84%
where it's actually
damaging and destructive.

00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:35.273 align:middle line:84%
So their delusion has
lots of conditions.

00:05:35.273 --> 00:05:36.190 align:middle line:90%
And those conditions--

00:05:36.190 --> 00:05:37.773 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about the damage,

00:05:37.773 --> 00:05:41.130 align:middle line:84%
that that kind of mindset
of creating reality is.

00:05:41.130 --> 00:05:43.230 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Well, if you're
protecting a fantasy,

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:45.068 align:middle line:84%
you don't want it
interfered with.

00:05:45.068 --> 00:05:46.860 align:middle line:84%
Because it's like your
reality happy bubble

00:05:46.860 --> 00:05:50.400 align:middle line:84%
place and all the
accouterments and phenomena

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:52.350 align:middle line:90%
that associate with that.

00:05:52.350 --> 00:05:54.660 align:middle line:84%
You have to defend it
because it's vulnerable,

00:05:54.660 --> 00:05:56.100 align:middle line:90%
because it's unreal.

00:05:56.100 --> 00:05:58.540 align:middle line:84%
And one of those things
is don't offend me.

00:05:58.540 --> 00:05:59.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:59.340 --> 00:06:02.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So don't
offend me in my bubble

00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:06.210 align:middle line:84%
because your offense is an
existential threat to my life.

00:06:06.210 --> 00:06:08.800 align:middle line:84%
Because if my belief
systems collapse--

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:12.450 align:middle line:84%
however pleasing and
pleasant, and apparently sort

00:06:12.450 --> 00:06:14.760 align:middle line:90%
of humane in modern era--

00:06:14.760 --> 00:06:17.380 align:middle line:84%
then I'm in a
difficult position.

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:19.680 align:middle line:84%
So that's most people's
opposition to the truth,

00:06:19.680 --> 00:06:23.820 align:middle line:84%
is that it actually interferes
with their spiritual

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:26.170 align:middle line:90%
and material delusions.

00:06:26.170 --> 00:06:27.400 align:middle line:90%
So they don't want the truth.

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:28.410 align:middle line:90%
They want fantasy.

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:31.920 align:middle line:84%
Most people I ever see anywhere
in the world in all walks

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:34.320 align:middle line:90%
of life, they want fantasy.

00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:35.340 align:middle line:90%
That's what people want.

00:06:35.340 --> 00:06:36.960 align:middle line:90%
They settle for a fantasy.

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:38.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
that is largely true.

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:40.780 align:middle line:84%
And it's like I said in
the open of the show,

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:42.540 align:middle line:90%
it's an archaic thought.

00:06:42.540 --> 00:06:45.670 align:middle line:84%
Hermetics themselves
are archaic in a sense,

00:06:45.670 --> 00:06:50.520 align:middle line:84%
because they strip you down
to the basic nature of reality

00:06:50.520 --> 00:06:54.000 align:middle line:84%
in so many ways, where
people are being encouraged

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.400 align:middle line:84%
through modern
life to go anywhere

00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:59.890 align:middle line:84%
except to the discovery of where
the nature of reality truly is.

00:06:59.890 --> 00:07:02.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is a
preference-driven world.

00:07:02.270 --> 00:07:03.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah, it is.

00:07:03.780 --> 00:07:06.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
in my early life,

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:09.590 align:middle line:84%
I was interested
in esoteric study--

00:07:09.590 --> 00:07:11.510 align:middle line:90%
hermetism, rosicrucianism--

00:07:11.510 --> 00:07:12.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, all of it.

00:07:12.990 --> 00:07:14.950 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --occultic
practices, lots of things.

00:07:14.950 --> 00:07:18.870 align:middle line:84%
But all the time behind
that was Christianity.

00:07:18.870 --> 00:07:22.710 align:middle line:84%
So if you're a hermetist, you're
dealing with Christianity.

00:07:22.710 --> 00:07:26.730 align:middle line:84%
And what I learned from my
esoteric Christian studies is

00:07:26.730 --> 00:07:29.760 align:middle line:84%
there's an enormous
difference between real,

00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:34.020 align:middle line:84%
pure Christian practice--
which is super jedi hard core

00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:34.820 align:middle line:90%
excellence--

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:35.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mystical.

00:07:35.820 --> 00:07:39.510 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --and the institution
of the church, which

00:07:39.510 --> 00:07:41.422 align:middle line:84%
is almost nothing to
do with Christianity.

00:07:41.422 --> 00:07:42.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Worlds apart, yeah.

00:07:42.630 --> 00:07:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So 2.4, 2.5
billion Christians--

00:07:46.050 --> 00:07:49.080 align:middle line:84%
I would say-- sadly,
don't really know

00:07:49.080 --> 00:07:51.510 align:middle line:84%
what true Christian
practice is because it's

00:07:51.510 --> 00:07:53.220 align:middle line:90%
hard to understand.

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:56.140 align:middle line:84%
I've studied the Bible
for 30 years now.

00:07:56.140 --> 00:07:57.990 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say I'm just
understanding it

00:07:57.990 --> 00:08:00.670 align:middle line:90%
now because it is coded.

00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:05.552 align:middle line:84%
It's not meant to be open in
its deeper layers to everyone.

00:08:05.552 --> 00:08:07.260 align:middle line:84%
And some Bible scholars
I know personally

00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:08.960 align:middle line:90%
would disagree with me on that.

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:11.440 align:middle line:84%
Because it's a book written
for every man, every woman.

00:08:11.440 --> 00:08:12.240 align:middle line:90%
I see that.

00:08:12.240 --> 00:08:15.660 align:middle line:84%
It is true in this
parable and moral fiber.

00:08:15.660 --> 00:08:19.480 align:middle line:84%
And a compass of righteous
behavior, good virtue,

00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:21.570 align:middle line:90%
integrity, no question.

00:08:21.570 --> 00:08:23.400 align:middle line:90%
But the deeper layers of it--

00:08:23.400 --> 00:08:29.340 align:middle line:84%
prophecy, knowing divinity,
birth, death, afterlife--

00:08:29.340 --> 00:08:33.600 align:middle line:84%
the supernatural presence of
evil and good in the world

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:39.809 align:middle line:84%
is unparalleled in its
potency and its profundity.

00:08:39.809 --> 00:08:42.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's not visible
to the average reader.

00:08:42.330 --> 00:08:44.952 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have to
have maturity, knowledge.

00:08:44.952 --> 00:08:46.410 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: You have
to have maturity

00:08:46.410 --> 00:08:48.360 align:middle line:84%
in your own experiential
life, but you also

00:08:48.360 --> 00:08:50.010 align:middle line:90%
need instruction as well.

00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:52.905 align:middle line:84%
Without Bible
scholarship instruction,

00:08:52.905 --> 00:08:54.780 align:middle line:84%
I don't know whether
I'd have ever understood

00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:56.610 align:middle line:90%
what it was actually saying.

00:08:56.610 --> 00:09:01.110 align:middle line:84%
And that opens up part of our
discussion about absolutism

00:09:01.110 --> 00:09:02.640 align:middle line:90%
and relativism.

00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:07.680 align:middle line:84%
Because one of the big
threats to empire society

00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:10.170 align:middle line:84%
today-- empire being
this system of control.

00:09:10.170 --> 00:09:13.500 align:middle line:84%
And it totally rules
mainstream life.

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:15.900 align:middle line:90%
A threat to that is absolutism.

00:09:15.900 --> 00:09:19.890 align:middle line:84%
And the absolutism of
something like Christianity

00:09:19.890 --> 00:09:23.110 align:middle line:84%
is a danger to
mainstream culture.

00:09:23.110 --> 00:09:25.260 align:middle line:84%
And it is a danger because
it pulls it to pieces.

00:09:25.260 --> 00:09:26.677 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or, not
to the religion,

00:09:26.677 --> 00:09:29.260 align:middle line:84%
Christianity, but to the actual
mystical meaning and practice

00:09:29.260 --> 00:09:30.060 align:middle line:90%
behind it.

00:09:30.060 --> 00:09:30.810 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: True Christianity.

00:09:30.810 --> 00:09:31.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: True.

00:09:31.610 --> 00:09:35.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: True, true esoteric
Christianity is Christianity.

00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:36.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: The church stuff
is a contamination of it.

00:09:38.550 --> 00:09:41.637 align:middle line:84%
So actual Christianity is
mystical esoteric Christianity.

00:09:41.637 --> 00:09:42.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, absolutely.

00:09:42.720 --> 00:09:44.100 align:middle line:90%
I hear you on that.

00:09:44.100 --> 00:09:47.660 align:middle line:84%
OK, let's go back to
reality for one more moment.

00:09:47.660 --> 00:09:51.120 align:middle line:84%
The five sense world,
a lot of people say,

00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:52.550 align:middle line:90%
forget the five sense world.

00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Really, it's just a
construct of the mind.

00:09:54.540 --> 00:09:56.010 align:middle line:90%
But you can touch a tree.

00:09:56.010 --> 00:09:59.010 align:middle line:84%
These are agreed-upon
realities if you're

00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:00.260 align:middle line:90%
going to live on Earth, right?

00:10:00.260 --> 00:10:01.840 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Yeah, they are
here for important purpose.

00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:03.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're here
for-- so let's talk

00:10:03.590 --> 00:10:07.050 align:middle line:84%
about the meaning behind the
construct of Earth's reality,

00:10:07.050 --> 00:10:11.880 align:middle line:84%
our five sense
tangible, sensual world

00:10:11.880 --> 00:10:13.360 align:middle line:84%
which everything
is produced from.

00:10:13.360 --> 00:10:14.160 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Sure.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:16.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you were
a teacher teaching

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:20.200 align:middle line:90%
real esoteric spiritual lore--

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:24.580 align:middle line:84%
L-O-R-E-- and life, you
would take newcomers--

00:10:24.580 --> 00:10:26.080 align:middle line:84%
whether they're
children, or whether

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:28.150 align:middle line:84%
they're in the 50's or
60's, it doesn't matter.

00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:30.730 align:middle line:84%
You would take them into
the natural landscape.

00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:36.580 align:middle line:84%
And you would say, nature
shows us God's imagination.

00:10:36.580 --> 00:10:38.330 align:middle line:90%
And it shows us it in two ways.

00:10:38.330 --> 00:10:40.960 align:middle line:84%
The first way is
that nature shows us

00:10:40.960 --> 00:10:44.320 align:middle line:90%
incredible unparalleled beauty.

00:10:44.320 --> 00:10:45.678 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:10:45.678 --> 00:10:48.220 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I could name so many
things, especially living in--

00:10:48.220 --> 00:10:50.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But that's a
virtue worth living for.

00:10:50.230 --> 00:10:51.030 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It it.

00:10:51.030 --> 00:10:52.430 align:middle line:84%
Beauty makes life
worth it often.

00:10:52.430 --> 00:10:53.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It does.

00:10:53.230 --> 00:10:55.522 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And when everything
else is broken and fallen

00:10:55.522 --> 00:10:58.390 align:middle line:84%
to pieces, as happens in
life, beauty is there.

00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:01.000 align:middle line:84%
So I take myself at
bad times in life

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:04.270 align:middle line:84%
to the mountains, the rivers,
the meadows, the pastures,

00:11:04.270 --> 00:11:06.070 align:middle line:90%
the forests, the deserts.

00:11:06.070 --> 00:11:07.690 align:middle line:90%
And I see incredible beauty.

00:11:07.690 --> 00:11:09.160 align:middle line:90%
I see harmony.

00:11:09.160 --> 00:11:10.300 align:middle line:90%
I see elegance.

00:11:10.300 --> 00:11:12.190 align:middle line:90%
I see love.

00:11:12.190 --> 00:11:16.120 align:middle line:84%
I see this enormous
ecology of life

00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:20.140 align:middle line:84%
where everything is finding
equilibrium and a sense

00:11:20.140 --> 00:11:21.390 align:middle line:90%
of goodness together.

00:11:21.390 --> 00:11:22.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:11:22.190 --> 00:11:23.690 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: That's
on the one hand.

00:11:23.690 --> 00:11:26.740 align:middle line:84%
There's a flip side to that,
which is nature also shows

00:11:26.740 --> 00:11:29.260 align:middle line:90%
us it is savage.

00:11:29.260 --> 00:11:30.880 align:middle line:90%
It is hostile.

00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:32.800 align:middle line:90%
It is parasitic.

00:11:32.800 --> 00:11:36.710 align:middle line:84%
And it cares nothing
for human life, nothing.

00:11:36.710 --> 00:11:40.330 align:middle line:84%
So if I go and hike in my
Olympic National Forest,

00:11:40.330 --> 00:11:42.100 align:middle line:84%
a cougar will come
and rip my throat out.

00:11:42.100 --> 00:11:44.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'm dead in a gully for two
weeks until somebody finds--

00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:45.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And it's not personal.

00:11:45.320 --> 00:11:46.300 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: It's not personal.

00:11:46.300 --> 00:11:47.260 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't know who I am.

00:11:47.260 --> 00:11:49.450 align:middle line:90%
It's not disagreeing with me.

00:11:49.450 --> 00:11:54.740 align:middle line:84%
It's just the hostile
nature of this landscape.

00:11:54.740 --> 00:11:56.180 align:middle line:90%
So nature shows you two things.

00:11:56.180 --> 00:11:59.170 align:middle line:84%
One is harmony, and
one is disharmony.

00:11:59.170 --> 00:12:02.800 align:middle line:84%
And the esoteric teaching in
that that nature reveals--

00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:05.920 align:middle line:84%
and this is a big thing to
say, but I'm happy to say it--

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:11.620 align:middle line:84%
what that shows us is that this
is not our natural environment.

00:12:11.620 --> 00:12:14.020 align:middle line:90%
This world is not our home.

00:12:14.020 --> 00:12:16.228 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's not
where the soul resides.

00:12:16.228 --> 00:12:18.520 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: It's not our home
in any way, shape, or form.

00:12:18.520 --> 00:12:21.880 align:middle line:84%
Soul is not here, although
the vessel of soul is here.

00:12:21.880 --> 00:12:23.070 align:middle line:90%
But what fills it?

00:12:23.070 --> 00:12:25.000 align:middle line:90%
Spirit is not here.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.230 align:middle line:90%
So our original home is gone.

00:12:27.230 --> 00:12:30.940 align:middle line:84%
This is a world of
teaching which is finite.

00:12:30.940 --> 00:12:32.230 align:middle line:90%
And then a new world comes.

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:35.200 align:middle line:84%
This world is meant
to be disharmonious.

00:12:35.200 --> 00:12:37.000 align:middle line:90%
Nature shows us that.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:41.890 align:middle line:84%
So this finiteness of this world
and the inherent brokenness

00:12:41.890 --> 00:12:43.840 align:middle line:90%
of it is the teaching mechanism.

00:12:43.840 --> 00:12:45.250 align:middle line:90%
Polarization.

00:12:45.250 --> 00:12:49.330 align:middle line:84%
Good, evil, right,
wrong, broken, whole.

00:12:49.330 --> 00:12:50.950 align:middle line:84%
That's the tough
thing in reality

00:12:50.950 --> 00:12:56.650 align:middle line:84%
that you have to realize as
Christ did, as Buddha did.

00:12:56.650 --> 00:13:01.270 align:middle line:84%
Christ says this world is
broken, but it's teaching.

00:13:01.270 --> 00:13:04.090 align:middle line:84%
Buddha says this world is
suffering, but it's teaching.

00:13:04.090 --> 00:13:06.610 align:middle line:84%
Don't try and pretend
it's not suffering.

00:13:06.610 --> 00:13:10.510 align:middle line:84%
Don't seek for a truth that's
like a bomb or a medicine

00:13:10.510 --> 00:13:12.800 align:middle line:90%
or a bandage for your suffering.

00:13:12.800 --> 00:13:15.760 align:middle line:84%
Understand that your suffering
will purify you and show you

00:13:15.760 --> 00:13:16.880 align:middle line:90%
truth.

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.640 align:middle line:84%
So you're changing
your relationship

00:13:18.640 --> 00:13:23.260 align:middle line:84%
with the pain of
reality to suffer less.

00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:25.750 align:middle line:90%
So you purify, you suffer less.

00:13:25.750 --> 00:13:28.900 align:middle line:84%
Now that is a tough teaching
that most people in this day

00:13:28.900 --> 00:13:31.300 align:middle line:90%
don't want to suffer at all.

00:13:31.300 --> 00:13:33.612 align:middle line:84%
They'll do anything
to avoid suffering.

00:13:33.612 --> 00:13:34.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Well, indeed.

00:13:34.570 --> 00:13:36.640 align:middle line:84%
And we have every single
distraction in the world

00:13:36.640 --> 00:13:37.600 align:middle line:90%
to help us avoid it.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:38.140 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: A million.

00:13:38.140 --> 00:13:39.682 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the
notion of suffering

00:13:39.682 --> 00:13:41.103 align:middle line:90%
also has to do with attachment.

00:13:41.103 --> 00:13:42.520 align:middle line:84%
And once we attach
to whether it's

00:13:42.520 --> 00:13:44.830 align:middle line:84%
an idea, a person,
a thing, or whatnot,

00:13:44.830 --> 00:13:46.990 align:middle line:84%
and that is being
removed from our reality,

00:13:46.990 --> 00:13:51.560 align:middle line:84%
that tends to create a lot
of what we call suffering.

00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:52.360 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Indeed.

00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:57.550 align:middle line:84%
And that, again, is a great
Hindu and Christian principle

00:13:57.550 --> 00:14:02.290 align:middle line:84%
shared well between those two
ways of perceiving reality.

00:14:02.290 --> 00:14:04.830 align:middle line:84%
For me, what my
Christian upbringing

00:14:04.830 --> 00:14:08.350 align:middle line:84%
showed me is that if
you attach yourself

00:14:08.350 --> 00:14:10.840 align:middle line:84%
to anything in this world,
you've made a big mistake.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:13.210 align:middle line:84%
Because this world--
as Paul told us,

00:14:13.210 --> 00:14:16.210 align:middle line:84%
as Christ told us, as Peter
told us-- is passing away.

00:14:16.210 --> 00:14:18.310 align:middle line:84%
So to invest in this
would be foolish.

00:14:18.310 --> 00:14:22.120 align:middle line:84%
Emotionally, mentally,
financially, materially, it

00:14:22.120 --> 00:14:23.230 align:middle line:90%
would be foolish.

00:14:23.230 --> 00:14:25.520 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, its
presence is important.

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:27.280 align:middle line:90%
It's a teaching mechanism.

00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:30.370 align:middle line:84%
Its illusionary
nature is irrelevant.

00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:31.665 align:middle line:90%
Its presence is what counts.

00:14:31.665 --> 00:14:36.160 align:middle line:84%
So to cast this off as
Maya, illusion, samsara,

00:14:36.160 --> 00:14:37.260 align:middle line:90%
is an error in my view.

00:14:37.260 --> 00:14:38.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
it's an error as well.

00:14:38.530 --> 00:14:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I think that
would be a mistake.

00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:41.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is
our learning ground.

00:14:41.170 --> 00:14:42.628 align:middle line:84%
It's our school
and our playground.

00:14:42.628 --> 00:14:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And to
live in a body that

00:14:44.710 --> 00:14:47.980 align:middle line:84%
is dying as soon as it
is born is incredible.

00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:49.880 align:middle line:84%
It's part of the
teaching mechanism.

00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:54.110 align:middle line:84%
So the very mortality of a
human being, 100 years of life--

00:14:54.110 --> 00:14:56.220 align:middle line:90%
a little less, a little more--

00:14:56.220 --> 00:14:57.280 align:middle line:90%
are not set.

00:14:57.280 --> 00:15:00.370 align:middle line:84%
And then, you know, you wake
up and your body's changing.

00:15:00.370 --> 00:15:02.110 align:middle line:90%
Your form changes.

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:03.250 align:middle line:90%
You have illness.

00:15:03.250 --> 00:15:04.360 align:middle line:90%
You have disease.

00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:07.060 align:middle line:90%
You have pain, sorrow.

00:15:07.060 --> 00:15:07.990 align:middle line:90%
People are born.

00:15:07.990 --> 00:15:09.100 align:middle line:90%
People die.

00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:10.360 align:middle line:90%
People come into our lives.

00:15:10.360 --> 00:15:12.110 align:middle line:90%
People go out of our lives.

00:15:12.110 --> 00:15:13.780 align:middle line:90%
This is the teaching.

00:15:13.780 --> 00:15:16.570 align:middle line:84%
None of these things are
separate from spiritual life.

00:15:16.570 --> 00:15:17.720 align:middle line:90%
They are spiritual life.

00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:18.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:20.830 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: So the
physical reality

00:15:20.830 --> 00:15:23.080 align:middle line:84%
is what we're being
asked to look at.

00:15:23.080 --> 00:15:25.790 align:middle line:84%
Now the spiritual
reality is there too.

00:15:25.790 --> 00:15:28.450 align:middle line:84%
But it's the physical
reality is forcing you

00:15:28.450 --> 00:15:30.760 align:middle line:90%
to embody your spiritual truth.

00:15:30.760 --> 00:15:32.800 align:middle line:84%
If it's not
embodied, if it's not

00:15:32.800 --> 00:15:37.570 align:middle line:84%
every day in your home-- in
the kitchen, in the workplace,

00:15:37.570 --> 00:15:40.370 align:middle line:84%
in the supermarket--
then it's not real.

00:15:40.370 --> 00:15:44.052 align:middle line:84%
So the physical compels you
to deal with what is real.

00:15:44.052 --> 00:15:45.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I couldn't
agree with you more.

00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:48.670 align:middle line:84%
It's engaging with life in
the five sensory world--

00:15:48.670 --> 00:15:50.230 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Embracing
the whole thing.

00:15:50.230 --> 00:15:50.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --where the
lessons are all of it.

00:15:50.650 --> 00:15:50.980 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yes.

00:15:50.980 --> 00:15:52.772 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so let
me ask you about this.

00:15:52.772 --> 00:15:55.180 align:middle line:84%
This is another overlay,
an esoteric one.

00:15:55.180 --> 00:15:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And Tom Campbell's work,
"My Big TOE", right?

00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:02.350 align:middle line:84%
The way he describes
reality as we experience

00:16:02.350 --> 00:16:05.890 align:middle line:84%
is a collectively
rendered reality.

00:16:05.890 --> 00:16:08.440 align:middle line:84%
Because the people who
are incarnating here

00:16:08.440 --> 00:16:10.600 align:middle line:84%
on this planet,
at this time, have

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:15.490 align:middle line:84%
chosen to have this playground
as our collective experience--

00:16:15.490 --> 00:16:18.220 align:middle line:84%
even if the tree is
no more a tree than it

00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:21.050 align:middle line:84%
is a shoe, if you just look
at it from a quantum physics

00:16:21.050 --> 00:16:21.850 align:middle line:90%
level.

00:16:21.850 --> 00:16:26.080 align:middle line:84%
So somehow we have all agreed
to play in this together.

00:16:26.080 --> 00:16:27.830 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I see that
a little differently.

00:16:27.830 --> 00:16:29.090 align:middle line:90%
I love Tom Campbell, by the way.

00:16:29.090 --> 00:16:29.890 align:middle line:90%
He totally rocks.

00:16:29.890 --> 00:16:32.540 align:middle line:84%
But I see it differently
to him on this one.

00:16:32.540 --> 00:16:33.610 align:middle line:90%
This is a made world.

00:16:33.610 --> 00:16:37.100 align:middle line:84%
It was designed and we
had nothing to do with it.

00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:38.742 align:middle line:90%
So I don't see that in that way.

00:16:38.742 --> 00:16:40.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I
mean, it is interesting

00:16:40.450 --> 00:16:42.610 align:middle line:84%
because that would
denote that we've

00:16:42.610 --> 00:16:44.330 align:middle line:90%
created the world around us.

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:45.360 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: We haven't.

00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:46.238 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:16:46.238 --> 00:16:48.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: In my life, I
see no evidence for that.

00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:51.280 align:middle line:90%
I go to my sources of wisdom--

00:16:51.280 --> 00:16:57.180 align:middle line:84%
me, God, wise men and women
I know, spiritual literature.

00:16:57.180 --> 00:16:59.660 align:middle line:84%
And none of those things
corroborate that for me.

00:16:59.660 --> 00:17:00.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:00.460 --> 00:17:06.190 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: The way I feel now is
that this world was agreed upon

00:17:06.190 --> 00:17:08.930 align:middle line:90%
to be in by our ancestors--

00:17:08.930 --> 00:17:10.978 align:middle line:84%
so the original man,
the original woman.

00:17:10.978 --> 00:17:12.520 align:middle line:84%
And again, you see
this in hermetism.

00:17:12.520 --> 00:17:14.710 align:middle line:90%
You see it in Christianity.

00:17:14.710 --> 00:17:16.630 align:middle line:84%
You see it in many
other systems.

00:17:16.630 --> 00:17:22.540 align:middle line:84%
Our ancestors made the decision
to know the wisdom of God,

00:17:22.540 --> 00:17:27.220 align:middle line:84%
to know the discriminating
power of good and evil,

00:17:27.220 --> 00:17:28.660 align:middle line:90%
to know those things.

00:17:28.660 --> 00:17:31.990 align:middle line:84%
We, therefore-- through
heritage and their endowment--

00:17:31.990 --> 00:17:34.600 align:middle line:84%
have come here to
complete that project.

00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:37.330 align:middle line:84%
To know good and evil, to know
right and wrong, to know truth

00:17:37.330 --> 00:17:40.840 align:middle line:84%
and falsehood in this
world that is expertly

00:17:40.840 --> 00:17:42.610 align:middle line:90%
made as a classroom--

00:17:42.610 --> 00:17:45.110 align:middle line:90%
to compel that to happen.

00:17:45.110 --> 00:17:47.130 align:middle line:90%
And the bad guys--

00:17:47.130 --> 00:17:49.670 align:middle line:84%
again, supernatural origin,
but the human administrators

00:17:49.670 --> 00:17:50.470 align:middle line:90%
of that--

00:17:50.470 --> 00:17:54.345 align:middle line:84%
all they have to do is persuade
you that that's all garbage.

00:17:54.345 --> 00:17:55.720 align:middle line:84%
And if that's what
you should do,

00:17:55.720 --> 00:17:58.930 align:middle line:84%
is look after your own comfort
and security and entertainment,

00:17:58.930 --> 00:18:00.200 align:middle line:90%
there is nothing to discern.

00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:01.900 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing to discriminate.

00:18:01.900 --> 00:18:03.880 align:middle line:84%
Good and evil is an
old-fashioned idea.

00:18:03.880 --> 00:18:05.207 align:middle line:90%
And frankly, it's gone away.

00:18:05.207 --> 00:18:06.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's subjective.

00:18:06.290 --> 00:18:07.750 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: They would
love you to think that.

00:18:07.750 --> 00:18:08.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:18:08.170 --> 00:18:09.850 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And as
soon as that happens,

00:18:09.850 --> 00:18:11.620 align:middle line:90%
you are de-spiritualizing.

