many years ago.

00:43:23.590 --> 00:43:25.430 align:middle line:84%
They're all-- that
generation is gone.

00:43:25.430 --> 00:43:26.230 align:middle line:90%
They've sold.

00:43:26.230 --> 00:43:27.390 align:middle line:90%
They're dying out.

00:43:27.390 --> 00:43:31.460 align:middle line:84%
But what's coming in, the people
coming in in their place--

00:43:31.460 --> 00:43:33.860 align:middle line:84%
and I'm seeing this
phenomenon all over now even

00:43:33.860 --> 00:43:35.240 align:middle line:90%
in magazines--

00:43:35.240 --> 00:43:41.420 align:middle line:84%
are mostly fundamentalist
Christian and Mormons,

00:43:41.420 --> 00:43:42.680 align:middle line:90%
in particular.

00:43:42.680 --> 00:43:46.280 align:middle line:84%
Our whole area has
families with 5, 6, 7

00:43:46.280 --> 00:43:49.220 align:middle line:90%
kids that have moved in.

00:43:49.220 --> 00:43:51.020 align:middle line:84%
But what's interesting
about it is they

00:43:51.020 --> 00:43:52.470 align:middle line:90%
can see what they're doing.

00:43:52.470 --> 00:43:58.762 align:middle line:84%
It's a backlash against the
world of untruths and chaotic--

00:43:58.762 --> 00:44:00.470 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Yeah, they're
overcompensating.

00:44:00.470 --> 00:44:01.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're
overcompensating.

00:44:01.580 --> 00:44:03.330 align:middle line:84%
And so they're trying
to get the kids--

00:44:03.330 --> 00:44:04.130 align:middle line:90%
which is beautiful.

00:44:04.130 --> 00:44:05.630 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to
get the kids back.

00:44:05.630 --> 00:44:07.250 align:middle line:84%
They raise little
goats and pigs.

00:44:07.250 --> 00:44:08.660 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I know, it's
a nice overcompensation.

00:44:08.660 --> 00:44:10.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's a nice
overcompensation,

00:44:10.400 --> 00:44:12.260 align:middle line:90%
but it is a compensation.

00:44:12.260 --> 00:44:14.120 align:middle line:84%
But I feel, in their
hearts, they're

00:44:14.120 --> 00:44:17.670 align:middle line:84%
just so weary of the
messaging outside.

00:44:17.670 --> 00:44:19.808 align:middle line:84%
They don't want their
kids to be exposed to it.

00:44:19.808 --> 00:44:22.100 align:middle line:84%
A lot them are homeschooling
for the exact same reason.

00:44:22.100 --> 00:44:26.300 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, almost
every family around us

00:44:26.300 --> 00:44:30.070 align:middle line:84%
now is back to land, back
to nature, Christianity--

00:44:30.070 --> 00:44:32.210 align:middle line:84%
but organized,
formal Christianity

00:44:32.210 --> 00:44:34.820 align:middle line:84%
in terms of religious
institutions.

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:35.700 align:middle line:90%
I understand it.

00:44:35.700 --> 00:44:36.500 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: I do.

00:44:36.500 --> 00:44:39.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, modern society,
especially in Europe

00:44:39.830 --> 00:44:43.130 align:middle line:84%
more than anywhere
else, is debauched.

00:44:43.130 --> 00:44:46.950 align:middle line:84%
And it is degenerate, I have
to say, especially in England,

00:44:46.950 --> 00:44:49.070 align:middle line:90%
France, Germany, Spain.

00:44:49.070 --> 00:44:53.150 align:middle line:84%
America don't realize how lucky
they are to have choices here.

00:44:53.150 --> 00:44:56.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Tell us about what
you mean by the debauchery,

00:44:56.030 --> 00:44:58.850 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, in the European
nations compared to the US.

00:44:58.850 --> 00:45:00.450 align:middle line:84%
Because most US
citizens would say,

00:45:00.450 --> 00:45:03.000 align:middle line:84%
well, that's happening here
to a large extent as well.

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:04.670 align:middle line:84%
What's the difference
between them?

00:45:04.670 --> 00:45:06.680 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: That's a
media illusion that's

00:45:06.680 --> 00:45:07.990 align:middle line:90%
been drawn over people's life.

00:45:07.990 --> 00:45:09.680 align:middle line:84%
Think, hey, you know,
secretly, we all

00:45:09.680 --> 00:45:12.020 align:middle line:84%
think that Britain
and Germany and France

00:45:12.020 --> 00:45:15.170 align:middle line:84%
are kind of like a bit more
sophisticated and a bit more

00:45:15.170 --> 00:45:18.580 align:middle line:84%
elegant and gracious-- and
have this history, and just

00:45:18.580 --> 00:45:19.860 align:middle line:90%
more civilized people.

00:45:19.860 --> 00:45:21.610 align:middle line:90%
Wrong, totally wrong.

00:45:21.610 --> 00:45:23.140 align:middle line:90%
Those people have been crushed.

00:45:23.140 --> 00:45:24.260 align:middle line:84%
And I know that because
I've lived there for--

00:45:24.260 --> 00:45:25.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, crushed by
their traditions, even.

00:45:25.720 --> 00:45:27.262 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --most of
my life have been

00:45:27.262 --> 00:45:32.740 align:middle line:84%
crushed by aristocratic
families who serve evil.

00:45:32.740 --> 00:45:34.072 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:45:34.072 --> 00:45:35.530 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: And that's
been unchanged

00:45:35.530 --> 00:45:37.960 align:middle line:90%
for at least two millennia.

00:45:37.960 --> 00:45:41.800 align:middle line:84%
What's different about America
is that although it was

00:45:41.800 --> 00:45:44.270 align:middle line:90%
certainly a naivete at times--

00:45:44.270 --> 00:45:47.350 align:middle line:84%
and if I may say, an
inelegance from time

00:45:47.350 --> 00:45:48.918 align:middle line:90%
to time in certain quarters--

00:45:48.918 --> 00:45:49.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And immaturity.

00:45:49.960 --> 00:45:50.750 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: --from an immaturity.

00:45:50.750 --> 00:45:52.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're still
growing our history.

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:55.030 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Just like a child who
went into a fancy restaurant

00:45:55.030 --> 00:45:58.790 align:middle line:84%
with clutter around, and not
know what fork to pick up.

00:45:58.790 --> 00:46:01.310 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't mean they're
bad, they just don't know yet.

00:46:01.310 --> 00:46:02.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're a young culture

00:46:02.400 --> 00:46:03.250 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:46:03.250 --> 00:46:05.050 align:middle line:84%
There's a gullibility
and a naivete,

00:46:05.050 --> 00:46:08.890 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes, an
ungrateful aspect to that.

00:46:08.890 --> 00:46:11.180 align:middle line:84%
But let me show you
the flip side of that.

00:46:11.180 --> 00:46:13.637 align:middle line:84%
There's a positivity,
a cheerfulness--

00:46:13.637 --> 00:46:14.595 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A creativity.

00:46:14.595 --> 00:46:16.960 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: --a creativity,
an opportunity

00:46:16.960 --> 00:46:19.360 align:middle line:84%
that does not exist
anywhere else in the world.

00:46:19.360 --> 00:46:20.810 align:middle line:90%
It's only in America.

00:46:20.810 --> 00:46:21.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:46:21.610 --> 00:46:25.600 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: I am much happier
to be an American citizen

00:46:25.600 --> 00:46:27.190 align:middle line:90%
than a British citizen.

00:46:27.190 --> 00:46:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And I'm proud to be in
this land of excellence,

00:46:30.550 --> 00:46:34.802 align:middle line:84%
which is exceptional in
its spiritual opportunity.

00:46:34.802 --> 00:46:36.510 align:middle line:84%
That there is nowhere
else in the world--

00:46:36.510 --> 00:46:39.550 align:middle line:84%
take my word for this-- where
you can have that except here.

00:46:39.550 --> 00:46:41.800 align:middle line:84%
We have to now look at
what's right and wrong.

00:46:41.800 --> 00:46:44.450 align:middle line:84%
Big political issues
about abortion,

00:46:44.450 --> 00:46:47.418 align:middle line:84%
about race, about
immigration, about borders--

00:46:47.418 --> 00:46:48.460 align:middle line:90%
what do they make you do?

00:46:48.460 --> 00:46:49.800 align:middle line:90%
They make you think about it.

00:46:49.800 --> 00:46:51.790 align:middle line:84%
They may think, well,
hang on a second.

00:46:51.790 --> 00:46:54.820 align:middle line:90%
Is it OK to have open borders?

00:46:54.820 --> 00:46:56.770 align:middle line:90%
What does that do to a country?

00:46:56.770 --> 00:46:57.910 align:middle line:90%
What is an open border?

00:46:57.910 --> 00:47:00.220 align:middle line:90%
What is a country even?

00:47:00.220 --> 00:47:02.770 align:middle line:84%
Now whatever you think about
that, that's a very, very

00:47:02.770 --> 00:47:04.300 align:middle line:90%
important question to ask.

00:47:04.300 --> 00:47:05.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it's
a very important--

00:47:05.380 --> 00:47:06.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Whatever
you think about that,

00:47:06.200 --> 00:47:08.500 align:middle line:84%
however kind and bring
everyone of the whole world

00:47:08.500 --> 00:47:12.470 align:middle line:84%
into my yard, or nobody except
people who look like me--

00:47:12.470 --> 00:47:13.270 align:middle line:90%
whatever.

00:47:13.270 --> 00:47:16.270 align:middle line:84%
One extreme or the other,
everything in between, they're

00:47:16.270 --> 00:47:18.580 align:middle line:84%
really important
questions to ask

00:47:18.580 --> 00:47:22.100 align:middle line:84%
which were never asked
in the common household

00:47:22.100 --> 00:47:23.650 align:middle line:90%
until recently.

00:47:23.650 --> 00:47:25.510 align:middle line:84%
In my kitchen table
with these people

00:47:25.510 --> 00:47:29.110 align:middle line:84%
I care about and the
things that we contemplate

00:47:29.110 --> 00:47:31.900 align:middle line:90%
in this home, what is a border?

00:47:31.900 --> 00:47:34.600 align:middle line:90%
What is death?

00:47:34.600 --> 00:47:36.730 align:middle line:90%
Is it murder killing a fetus?

00:47:36.730 --> 00:47:38.230 align:middle line:84%
Or does it have to
be a certain age?

00:47:38.230 --> 00:47:40.090 align:middle line:90%
Or is that health care?

00:47:40.090 --> 00:47:43.190 align:middle line:90%
Is that reproductive well-being?

00:47:43.190 --> 00:47:44.320 align:middle line:90%
What even is that?

00:47:44.320 --> 00:47:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And to have people
asking those questions

00:47:46.780 --> 00:47:48.400 align:middle line:90%
is incredibly important.

00:47:48.400 --> 00:47:50.890 align:middle line:90%
Because truth leads to reality.

00:47:50.890 --> 00:47:55.853 align:middle line:84%
Reality is the body,
the imagination of God.

00:47:55.853 --> 00:47:56.770 align:middle line:90%
What are those things?

00:47:56.770 --> 00:47:57.770 align:middle line:90%
Well, let's define them.

00:47:57.770 --> 00:47:59.180 align:middle line:90%
Let's look at them.

00:47:59.180 --> 00:48:00.850 align:middle line:84%
If people are doing
that, we're going

00:48:00.850 --> 00:48:04.160 align:middle line:84%
to come to a consensus,
which is true.

00:48:04.160 --> 00:48:08.140 align:middle line:84%
We're going to find common
ground, which is substantial.

00:48:08.140 --> 00:48:09.760 align:middle line:84%
We're going to say,
OK, if you have

00:48:09.760 --> 00:48:12.080 align:middle line:84%
a preference against
this culture, this music,

00:48:12.080 --> 00:48:12.880 align:middle line:90%
you know what?

00:48:12.880 --> 00:48:17.440 align:middle line:84%
That's fine because there's
common ground of moral virtue,

00:48:17.440 --> 00:48:21.340 align:middle line:84%
of decency, of civility,
of human creativity.

00:48:21.340 --> 00:48:23.510 align:middle line:90%
And potential is huge.

00:48:23.510 --> 00:48:25.990 align:middle line:84%
If you don't want to vote
Republican or Democrat,

00:48:25.990 --> 00:48:27.230 align:middle line:90%
that's fine.

00:48:27.230 --> 00:48:29.920 align:middle line:84%
We're all really
libertarians, in that we

00:48:29.920 --> 00:48:30.930 align:middle line:90%
are the sovereign power.

00:48:30.930 --> 00:48:31.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:48:31.240 --> 00:48:32.040 align:middle line:90%
I detest politics.

00:48:32.040 --> 00:48:33.603 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: We are
the sovereign power.

00:48:33.603 --> 00:48:35.020 align:middle line:84%
There is a sovereign
above us that

00:48:35.020 --> 00:48:37.720 align:middle line:84%
grants us that power in
virtue as an endowment,

00:48:37.720 --> 00:48:40.180 align:middle line:90%
as a graceful emanation.

00:48:40.180 --> 00:48:43.240 align:middle line:84%
And all of us are
equal in that regard--

00:48:43.240 --> 00:48:44.320 align:middle line:90%
all of us.

00:48:44.320 --> 00:48:47.140 align:middle line:84%
The difference is, if you
don't ask those questions

00:48:47.140 --> 00:48:50.590 align:middle line:84%
and you don't have common
ground, then our differences--

00:48:50.590 --> 00:48:53.350 align:middle line:84%
our ethnic and racial and
intellectual and physical

00:48:53.350 --> 00:48:56.500 align:middle line:84%
differences--
become separations.

00:48:56.500 --> 00:48:57.710 align:middle line:90%
They needn't be.

00:48:57.710 --> 00:49:00.010 align:middle line:84%
They're complementary
to each other.

00:49:00.010 --> 00:49:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
thing that when we

00:49:01.510 --> 00:49:04.660 align:middle line:84%
ask these questions,
forced by what's

00:49:04.660 --> 00:49:07.300 align:middle line:84%
on the television and
newspapers, is good.

00:49:07.300 --> 00:49:08.990 align:middle line:90%
So I remain optimistic in this.

00:49:08.990 --> 00:49:12.140 align:middle line:84%
Even though I think this game
is drawing to its conclusion--

00:49:12.140 --> 00:49:14.947 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you again, the
whole thing forever--

00:49:14.947 --> 00:49:16.780 align:middle line:84%
I think that's a good
thing because it means

00:49:16.780 --> 00:49:19.180 align:middle line:90%
that the classroom is finished.

00:49:19.180 --> 00:49:20.250 align:middle line:90%
We've graduated.

00:49:20.250 --> 00:49:21.370 align:middle line:90%
Enough people.

00:49:21.370 --> 00:49:23.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not many, but the
critical mass of people

00:49:23.740 --> 00:49:25.120 align:middle line:90%
is now in existence.

00:49:25.120 --> 00:49:29.050 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as that number
is reached, this is gone.

00:49:29.050 --> 00:49:30.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, then
a final statement

00:49:30.550 --> 00:49:31.810 align:middle line:90%
because we are out of time.

00:49:31.810 --> 00:49:34.690 align:middle line:84%
And that is, you
believe it is our duty

00:49:34.690 --> 00:49:37.170 align:middle line:84%
to begin discerning right
and wrong-- our duty.

00:49:37.170 --> 00:49:38.920 align:middle line:10%
>>KRAMER: It says we
have a responsibility

00:49:38.920 --> 00:49:43.840 align:middle line:10%
to know right and wrong, good
and evil, truth and falsehood.

00:49:43.840 --> 00:49:45.550 align:middle line:90%
You have to do it your own way.

00:49:45.550 --> 00:49:49.242 align:middle line:84%
You should seek wise
counsel on that from living,

00:49:49.242 --> 00:49:50.950 align:middle line:84%
breathing people you
can sit in front of.

00:49:50.950 --> 00:49:52.810 align:middle line:90%
Don't trust YouTube.

00:49:52.810 --> 00:49:54.160 align:middle line:90%
You can go to scripture.

00:49:54.160 --> 00:49:58.370 align:middle line:84%
You can speak to your own
heart and mind about that.

00:49:58.370 --> 00:50:03.250 align:middle line:84%
But your duty to know good and
evil makes this world better.

00:50:03.250 --> 00:50:05.952 align:middle line:84%
If you avoid that and
try not to offend people,

00:50:05.952 --> 00:50:07.660 align:middle line:84%
and don't say things
that are difficult--

00:50:07.660 --> 00:50:10.030 align:middle line:90%
don't go against the grain--

00:50:10.030 --> 00:50:12.040 align:middle line:90%
you perpetuate the problem.

00:50:12.040 --> 00:50:15.670 align:middle line:84%
So knowing good and evil,
exercising that discernment,

00:50:15.670 --> 00:50:19.190 align:middle line:90%
is a spiritual life.

00:50:19.190 --> 00:50:20.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with you.

00:50:20.570 --> 00:50:22.510 align:middle line:84%
And I always love
our conversations.

00:50:22.510 --> 00:50:24.830 align:middle line:84%
And they always
stretch people a bit.

00:50:24.830 --> 00:50:26.770 align:middle line:84%
And it also requires
nuanced thinking,

00:50:26.770 --> 00:50:28.900 align:middle line:84%
and that we're not
encouraged toward that.

00:50:28.900 --> 00:50:31.748 align:middle line:84%
And so again, Neil, I love
spending time with you.

00:50:31.748 --> 00:50:33.790 align:middle line:84%
We could probably go on
another five or six hours

00:50:33.790 --> 00:50:35.330 align:middle line:90%
on all of this.

00:50:35.330 --> 00:50:36.130 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:50:36.130 --> 00:50:37.535 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Thank you.

00:50:37.535 --> 00:50:39.910 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: I hope this has been
an intriguing conversation

00:50:39.910 --> 00:50:40.210 align:middle line:10%
for you.

00:50:40.210 --> 00:50:42.293 align:middle line:10%
I know it can be a bit
challenging, that time when

00:50:42.293 --> 00:50:43.300 align:middle line:10%
Neil and I get together.

00:50:43.300 --> 00:50:46.540 align:middle line:84%
But I really feel we need to
go more deeply into reflections

00:50:46.540 --> 00:50:49.960 align:middle line:84%
on the nature of reality and the
nature of good and evil itself.

00:50:49.960 --> 00:50:51.890 align:middle line:10%
To go there with Neil,
you can find his work

00:50:51.890 --> 00:50:52.690 align:middle line:10%
at neilkramer.com.

00:50:52.690 --> 00:50:56.260 align:middle line:10%
And you can find his
film, "Transmutation"

00:50:56.260 --> 00:50:57.810 align:middle line:10%
at transmutationfilm.com.

00:50:57.810 --> 00:51:00.670 align:middle line:10%
Until next time, thank
you for joining us here

00:51:00.670 --> 00:51:02.530 align:middle line:10%
on "Open Minds".

